<http://model.geneontology.org/R-HSA-375281/R-HSA-375281>
        a       <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_0008150> , <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual> ;
        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>
                "The class A (rhodopsin-like) GPCRs that bind to hormone ligands are annotated here. The hormones follicle-stimulating hormone (FSH), luteinizing hormone (LH), thyroid-stimulating hormone (TSH) and human chorionic gonadotrophin (hCG) are dimeric glycoproteins, sharing an identical alpha subunit and varying beta subunits. Their actions are mediated by the respective GPCRs, influencing reproductive processes and thyroid hormone release." ;
        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label>
                "Hormone ligand-binding receptors" ;
        <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/contributor>
